cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortTable
cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortTable.description: This table contains TBOP Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTTBOPPortEntry.description: Each PortEntry contains the configuration parameters for one TBOP port.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortNumber
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortNumber.description: Port number of the port being used by TBOP.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIAOpt.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIAOpt
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIAOpt.description: Specifies the control signal handshake and clocking required for a connection to be made to this port legal values are : simp - Simple, no control signals required. dtr - Dedicated, require the data terminal ready signal (DTR). dtrd - Same as DTR, except data set ready (DSR) drops between calls. dtrp - Same as DTR, except DSR/DCD/CTS are held low in the idle state. newvalSimp - same functionality as 'simp', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility. nc - Parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockType.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockType
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockType.description: int - internal clock source. ext - external clock source. newval - same functionality as 'int', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility. nc - parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockSpeed.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockSpeed
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, Clock Source = int. Legal Range=1200-384000. A value 0 indicates parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortTxCoding.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortTxCoding
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortTxCoding.description: This is the data encoding used on the TBOP port. nrz - Non Return to Zero. nrzi - Non Return to Zero Inverted. newvalNrz - same functionality as 'nrz', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility. nc - Parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortByteCount.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortByteCount
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortByteCount.description: This is the number of bytes collected from the line before data is forwarded. Legal values are : 128, 256, 384, 512, 640, 768, 896, 1036 and 1045. A value 0 indicates the parameter is not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIASigAction.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIASigAction
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEIASigAction.description: This specifies the EIA signaling actions allowed on the port: NONE - none SWITCH - switched carrier CTS - raise CTS in response to RTS A combination of CTS and SWITCH may be specified by summing (e.g. SWITCH+CTS). NC - Indicates the parameter not configued.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortOptions.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortOptions
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortOptions.description: Select options on this TBOP port as follows: none - port uses flag idle between frame exchanges and operates with as little as 2 idle flags between frames. marki - port uses mark idle between frame exchanges. (Required by System 36 - AS/400 series). cbr - for constant bit rate applications, the port operates with as little as 1 idle flag between frames. Also, if the outbound queue overflows, all frames on this queue will be purged. newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility. nc - parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortRTSCTSDelay.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortRTSCTSDelay
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortRTSCTSDelay.description: This specifies how long the TBOP port will delay CTS after RTS is raised when EIA Signaling Action = CTS. The delay is specified in 50 milliseconds units (1 = 50 milliseconds). Legal Range = 2-200. A value 0 indicates parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortDcdOnDelay.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortDcdOnDelay
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortDcdOnDelay.description: This specifies the length of time that DCD is held high before data is transmitted to the attached device. This is used when EIA Signaling Action = SWITCH. The delay is specified in milliseconds. Legal Range=1-255. A value 0 indicates parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallMnem.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallMnem
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallMnem.description: This mnemonic name is used for auto calling.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallTO.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallTO
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortAutoCallTO.description: This is the time interval in seconds between call attempts when auto calling.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxAutoTries.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxAutoTries
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxAutoTries.description: This specifies the number of times the TBOP port will attempt to call. A value of 0 will allow unlimited attempts.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortSubAddress.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortSubAddress
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortSubAddress.description: Calls addressed to this node, with this subaddress will be routed to this TBOP port.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortCUG.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortCUG
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortCUG.description: The TBOP port may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups. Each CUG membership must be a two digit number (except --) and separated by a comma. ( e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03 ). -- - No CUG Membership 00-99 - CUG Membership

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEnableBill.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEnableBill
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortEnableBill.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this TBOP port. newvalOff - same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxRxQSize.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxRxQSize
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxRxQSize.description: This parameter should be used with extreme caution. If using a non-default value, it is assumed you have discussed your application requirements with the manufacturer's support staff. A non-default value may result in excessive consumption of buffers, which can significantly impair the operation of all traffic over the node. This parameter defines the maximum number of frames which the inbound queue will contain. Frames are placed in this queue when they cannot be forwarded to the network link. If pipelining is enabled, this queue may contain frame segments. Therefore with pipelining enabled, this queue will typicaly contain more entries during network congestion. The default value of zero will result in a queue size between 32 and 100 depending on available memory. Legal Range=0,16-500. A value 501 indicates parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxTxQSize.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxTxQSize
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxTxQSize.description: This defines the maximum number of frames which the outbound queue will contain. These frames are recombined frames, as they were originaly received by the remote TBOP port.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortChanT1E1_Conn.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortChanT1E1_Conn
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortChanT1E1_Conn.description: This specifies whether a frame check sequence is generated for transmitted frames and whether the frame check sequence is stripped from received frames. It should be set to YES when connecting to a virtual TBOP port which maps to a T1 or E1 port. YES - Generate FCS for transmitted frames and strip FCS from received frames. NO - Don't generate FCS for transmitted frames or strip FCS from received frames. NC - Indicates the parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortIdleFlagCount.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortIdleFlagCount
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortIdleFlagCount.description: The Minimum number of Idle flags between frames. If MARKi option is used, this should be greater or equal to 2 and this many number of Idle flags will be inserted between frames apart from Mark Flag(FF)s. Legal Range = 1-15. A value 0 indicates parameter not configured.

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortElectricalInterfaceTyp.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortElectricalInterfaceTyp.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortV24ElectricalInterface.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortV24ElectricalInterface.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortHighSpeedElectricalInt.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortHighSpeedElectricalInt.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxFrameSize.name: cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxFrameSize
cdx6500TBOPCfgPortMaxFrameSize.description: This defines the maximum frame size which can be received by TBOP. The frame size is defined as the total number of octets in between flags. This parameter must be programmed as an even value. Legal Range = 1036-16384. A value 0 indicates the parameter not configured.

cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortTable
cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortTable.description: This table holds statistics items for TBOP ports

cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTTBOPPortEntry.description: This entry holds the statistics items for one TBOP port.

cdx6500TBOPStPortNumber.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortNumber
cdx6500TBOPStPortNumber.description: The port number for this TBOP entry.

cdx6500TBOPStPortStatus.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortStatus
cdx6500TBOPStPortStatus.description: Specifies current port Status. Up : Port is enabled by the CTP Disabled : Port is disabled by CTP Busy Out : The port is busy out by the CTP Down : Port is not enabled disables, or busy out by the CTP. Note : Port Status indicates Down state only if the TBOP port CMEM record entry portEnable gets corrupted.

cdx6500TBOPStPortState.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortState
cdx6500TBOPStPortState.description: The EIA state of the port.

cdx6500TBOPStPortSpeed.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortSpeed
cdx6500TBOPStPortSpeed.description: The measured port speed in bits per second.

cdx6500TBOPStOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500TBOPStOverrunErrors
cdx6500TBOPStOverrunErrors.description: Total number of overrun errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500TBOPStUnderrunErrors.name: cdx6500TBOPStUnderrunErrors
cdx6500TBOPStUnderrunErrors.description: Total number of underrun errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500TBOPStCRCErrors.name: cdx6500TBOPStCRCErrors
cdx6500TBOPStCRCErrors.description: Total number of CRC errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500TBOPStPortRxChars.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortRxChars
cdx6500TBOPStPortRxChars.description: Total number of data characters received since last boot or statistics reset, header characters are not included.

cdx6500TBOPStPortRxCharsSec.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortRxCharsSec
cdx6500TBOPStPortRxCharsSec.description: The average number of characters received per second.

cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFrames.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFrames
cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFrames.description: Total number of SDLC frames received since last boot or statistices reset.

cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFramesSec.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFramesSec
cdx6500TBOPStPortRxFramesSec.description: The average number of frames received per second.

cdx6500TBOPStPortTxChars.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortTxChars
cdx6500TBOPStPortTxChars.description: Total number of data characters transmitted since last boot or statistics reset, header characters are not included.

cdx6500TBOPStPortTxCharsSec.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortTxCharsSec
cdx6500TBOPStPortTxCharsSec.description: The average number of characters transmitted per second.

cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFrames.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFrames
cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFrames.description: Total number of SDLC frames trnsmitted since last boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFramesSec.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFramesSec
cdx6500TBOPStPortTxFramesSec.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second.

cdx6500TBOPStPortRxUtil.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortRxUtil
cdx6500TBOPStPortRxUtil.description: Percentage of port receive bandwidth used.

cdx6500TBOPStPortTxUtil.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortTxUtil
cdx6500TBOPStPortTxUtil.description: Percentage of port transmit bandwidth used.

cdx6500TBOPStPortFramesQueued.name: cdx6500TBOPStPortFramesQueued
cdx6500TBOPStPortFramesQueued.description: Number of SDLC frames queued to the I/O drivers.
